# Vite + Vue 3 — Project Rules

## Stack
- Vite 5 + Vue 3 (Composition API + <script setup>)
- Pinia for state management
- Vue Router 4 for routing
- Tailwind CSS 3 with custom design tokens
- No class-based components, no Options API

## Vue 3 Patterns

### Always use <script setup>
Every component uses <script setup> — never options API, never setup() return objects.

### Composable-first logic
Extract reusable reactive logic into /src/composables/use*.js files.
Components should be thin orchestrators, not logic holders.

### Props & Emits
Always define props with defineProps() and emits with defineEmits() — typed, explicit, documented.
Use camelCase for props in script, kebab-case in templates.

### Reactivity
Prefer ref() for primitives, reactive() only for complex plain objects.
Always use storeToRefs() when destructuring Pinia store state to keep reactivity.
Never mutate props — emit events or call store actions.

### Component naming
- PascalCase filenames: CustomerTable.vue
- Multi-word component names only (no single-word names)
- Group by feature then type: components/customers/CustomerTable.vue

### Template discipline
- No logic in templates beyond simple ternaries
- Extract v-for key logic into computed properties when non-trivial
- Use v-bind shorthand (:) and v-on shorthand (@) always

## Vite

### Aliases
Always use @/ alias for src/ imports. No relative ../../ paths beyond one level.

### Dynamic imports
Use dynamic import() for route-level code splitting:
  component: () => import('@/views/SomeView.vue')

### Environment variables
Only use import.meta.env.VITE_* for client-side env vars.
Never expose secrets — only prefix public vars with VITE_.

## State (Pinia)

### Setup stores only
Use the setup store syntax (defineStore with a setup function), not options stores.
Keep actions as named functions inside the store, not anonymous callbacks.

### Store granularity
One store per domain entity (customers, campaigns, insights).
Stores own their data and filtering logic — views orchestrate, stores own state.

## File structure
src/
├── assets/          # CSS, fonts, static
├── components/
│   ├── layout/      # SideNavBar, TopNavBar, etc.
│   ├── ui/          # Generic atoms: StatusBadge, MaterialIcon, etc.
│   └── [feature]/   # Feature-specific molecules
├── composables/     # use*.js composable hooks
├── mocks/           # Mock data — all mocks live here, exported from index
├── router/          # Route definitions
├── stores/          # Pinia stores
└── views/           # Route-level page components

## CSS / Tailwind

### Design token discipline
Never hardcode hex values in templates. Always use the Tailwind design token (bg-primary, text-on-surface).
Exceptions: one-off layout values like w-64 for sidebar width.

### Utility extraction
If a set of utilities repeats 3+ times, extract it to an @layer components class in main.css.
Never create a new CSS file for component styles unless it's a global base rule.

### No scoped styles for Tailwind-based components
Since we use utility classes, <style scoped> is only acceptable for
CSS-only interactions not achievable with utilities (e.g., custom keyframes).

## Code quality

### No magic strings
Status values, route names, filter keys — all must be constants defined in a central place (mocks/ or a constants/ file).

### No prop drilling beyond 2 levels
If a value needs to go deeper than 2 component levels, move it to a Pinia store or provide/inject.

### Async handling
All async operations must handle loading and error states.
Use a composable (useAsync or similar) to avoid repeating try/catch boilerplate.
